comment:
* Handles the response to * {@link AutofillService#onSavedDatasetsInfoRequest(SavedDatasetsInfoCallback)}. *

* Use {@link #onSuccess(Set)} to return the computed info about the datasets the user saved to this * service. If there was an error querying the info, or if the service is unable to do so at this * time (for example, if the user isn't logged in), call {@link #onError(int)}. *

* This callback can be used only once.

variables.name: ERROR_OTHER
variables.comment: * The result could not be computed for any other reason.

variables.name: ERROR_UNSUPPORTED
variables.comment: * The service does not support this request.

variables.name: ERROR_NEEDS_USER_ACTION
variables.comment:
* The result cannot be computed until the user takes some action, such as setting up their
     * account.

methods.name: void onSuccess(@NonNull Set<SavedDatasetsInfo> results)
methods.comment: * Successfully respond to the request with the info on each type of saved datasets.

methods.name: void onError(@Error int error)
methods.comment:
* Respond to the request with an error. System settings may display a suitable notice to the
     * user.
